input_str: It hasn’t been a very good week for Donald Trump. The GOP candidate was recently likened to Adolf Hitler by Eva Schloss, Anne Frank’s stepsister, and the 86-year-old Holocaust survivor also said Trump acted like the former leader of Nazi Germany. Now, according to a new Gallup poll, three out of every five Americans view Donald Trump unfavorably — a number that is higher than any nominated candidate from either major political party since Gallup began tracking favorability in 1992
